Also, with the introspection like u/kakkacarrotcake11 said, it‚Äôs important to sometimes take a step back as well to avoid going into a full blown panic and feelings of existential dread. Also the thing about going outside (the big outside where you can really keep that mmmcht *chef‚Äôs kiss* distance) is so true, something about sunshine and fresh air. I understand but ‚Äúgreat communication‚Äù isn‚Äôt always gushing and apologetic language. Maybe it‚Äôs fast straightforward replies. But maybe they‚Äôre not sorry that they don‚Äôt ship to Australia, and maybe they never will. That‚Äôs what I‚Äôm trying to highlight, you can‚Äôt just expect people to fluff their words and personalities for YOUR feelings. No is a full and complete answer in fact. Maybe ‚ÄúNo I‚Äôm afraid not‚Äù would suit your fancy better, but maybe they‚Äôre not the type to talk like that.

You see what I‚Äôm saying? You guys are cutthroat and too egocentric sometimes. The seller wasn‚Äôt mean or rude, they didn‚Äôt ‚ÄúNo i fucking don‚Äôt‚Äù, just ‚ÄúNo‚Äù... the world doesn‚Äôt cater to you I‚Äôm afraid, not everyone‚Äôs as empathic or attuned to sensitive nuances.

I don‚Äôt agree with the words you‚Äôre putting in my mouth. I don‚Äôt think the women who are ‚Äúokay‚Äù with this are subhumans who aren‚Äôt hurt by RAPE ‚Äúlike I am‚Äù. I don‚Äôt know how you turned me saying some people can manage to engage in casual sex then think nothing if it into me thinking there are women who are okay to rape. That‚Äôs sick, and I don‚Äôt understand where you found the crack to force that mentality into my discourse.

I know one camgirl and that‚Äôs where my ‚Äúmaybe some girls aren‚Äôt completely torn down by it‚Äù came from. I don‚Äôt know all women and I don‚Äôt know how all of them act or affected by things, and just because they aren‚Äôt affected by the same things I am doesn‚Äôt mean I think they‚Äôre less than me, which is what you‚Äôre saying I believe. Of course if they turn to sexwork because that‚Äôs all they have that‚Äôs terrible, I don‚Äôt revel in the fact that people to have to do sex work to survive.

I‚Äôm sure their bodies get sore like mine. All I‚Äôm acknowledging is that people are different, and I‚Äôm saying there are certainly women who have other avenues but still do sex work. What‚Äôs the explanation there? You can‚Äôt speak for all women nor can I.

I‚Äôm conflicted because it‚Äôs like, who am I to look down on these people‚Äôs lifestyles and tell them it‚Äôs wrong or to do something else? I do agree that it‚Äôs way more damaging than good and I would never encourage someone to participate in it but I don‚Äôt want to tear down individual sex workers. Pimps and such are an entirely different story, there‚Äôs absolutely no way such an organizational work structure is healthy and should indubitably remain illegal.

But the rise of Only Fans and such allows individuals to take sex work into their own hands and while I don‚Äôt see it as a viable or sensible means of life, I won‚Äôt talk down on them or bash them for their choices, but indeed deep down inside I do wish they chose better.

And who am I to speak to what traumatizes people individually? Like the issue of hookup culture vs monogamy, one night stands work for some people and for others it leaves them feeling empty, if that make sense...

What are they supposed to do? Embellish the answer like ‚Äúno I‚Äôm so sorry! I apologize, I wish I could!‚Äù Why do you want to force that behaviour on them? It‚Äôs a straightforward simple answer and the seller didn‚Äôt even end it with a period which more signifies tension. Why does it upset you? And these are genuine questions not rhetorical
